<font color="#FF0000">THANKS TO MR. VANARELLI</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  1 20:31:05 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I would just like to thank Mr. Varanelli for doing the ultimate. I am a Military soldier and served my country in Iraq. I was a Tank Commander on an M1A1 Main Battle Tank during Desert Storm.  I am both thankful and sad when I say that our Homecoming was very gratuitous. Yes we were Warriors as those from Vietnam were. They were Warriors far more deserving than us. My father-in-law of 11 years spent three tours in Nam. Two as a Marine (sniper-recon) and one as a Army soldier. He finished his carreer and retired as a CSM in the Army with 30 years. He retired in 1988 and to this day looks to be in his late thirties early forties.  He doesn't talk about the war at all. Even to me and I'm a veteran! <br>
     I was fortunate to visit the Wall in D.C. a couple of years ago and as I approached the walkway and began to look at the names on the wall I became weak and had chills running up and down my spine. The feeling is undescribable!<br><br>
     I SALUTE Mr. Arthur Vanarelli with all my HEART and all the other WARRIORS OF VIETNAM and you have my sincere GRATITUDE!!<br><br>
     I currently have 14 years of Active Service and intend on finishing at least six more.<br><br>
     I can be reached at  dawgmg7sfc@fuse.net<br><br>
